00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
meet the Scottish Crossbill the only

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:05.000
bird species unique to the United

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Kingdom dwelling in the ancient Pine

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:09.000
forests of Scotland this elusive bird is

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.000
a true Highlander with its distinctive

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:14.000
cross Bill the Scottish cross bill is

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:17.000
perfectly adapted to PRI seeds from pine

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:20.000
cones which form the bulk of its diet

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:22.000
this unique adaptation ensures they

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:25.000
thrive in their coniferous home avoiding

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.000
competition for food male Scottish

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:31.000
crossbills boast a vibrant red Hue while

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:33.000
females and young are colored a more

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:36.000
subdued greenish Brown blending

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:38.000
seamlessly with their Forest

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:41.000
surroundings their song a series of

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.000
trills and chirps adds to the Mystique

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:46.000
of the Scottish Woodlands conservation

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:48.000
efforts are crucial for this species as

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.000
they are entirely dependent on the

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.000
health of Scotland's Pine

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:55.000
forests protecting these habitats is not

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:58.000
just about preserving a bird but

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.000
safeguarding a symbol of Scottish

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.000
natural heritage